    Bartosz Milewski Says:

    November 30, 2015 at 10:33 am

    @sestu: Mac Lane has examples from various branches of mathematics: vector spaces, groups, rings, etc., but these are not essential to understanding his main ideas. Having said that, it‚Äôs a book for a working mathematician, which means it‚Äôs written in a very terse style. Without some experience in reading math papers, it‚Äôs very hard to follow. As a more gentle introduction, I would suggest Lawvere and Schanuel, Conceptual Mathematics .
