    @BartoszMilewski I‚Äôm wondering, how long it took you to learn all of that? Or were you born with that knowledge? =)

    I must say, I‚Äôm struggling a bit with concepts, I‚Äôm reading aside books about the theory, returning to your posts, rethinking something‚Ä¶ I see though that it‚Äôs useful, and I‚Äôm curious, how long it took for you to came to that level, and was it actually hard? What did you do in the absence of blog posts by Bartosz Milewski?
    Bartosz Milewski Says:

    July 28, 2016 at 8:33 am

    @Constantine: It took me a very long time. Not so much category theory itself ‚Äî that I started studying just a few years ago ‚Äî but the general background in mathematics. I went to a high school with extended program in mathematics, where I learned the basics of logic, axiomatic theory, geometry and calculus. Then I studied physics, which involved a lot of higher math. I was taught calculus through Banach and Hilbert spaces, and algebra through group theory and fibre bundles. So I had a very strong background in math when I switched to programming.

    Do I struggle reading math books and articles? You bet! But I just keep at it and don‚Äôt give up. The trick is not to think about the ultimate goal, but to enjoy the process of learning. This has become so much easier nowadays, with all the resources available through the internet.
